Html: Hey everyone, this is my first post in the PHPExcel discussion board, so excuse me if I forget to post important information.  Anyway, It seems that when I use the getSheetCount() and getSheetNames() methods PHPExcel returns a worksheet that does not exist in my document.  The spreadsheet I am using has only 2 worksheets in it, each with a specific name.  When PHPExcel reads the worksheets, it returns my 2 named worksheets and a generic "Sheet3" that does not exist in my document (verified in Office 2003, Office 2007 and OpenOffice 3.2).  Is this a bug in PHPExcel or do I have something configured wrong?
